OUT! Caught at leg gully! Out of nowhere, a wicket has fallen. Rabada has struck for the Proteas. It has taken 31 overs but a wicket has gone at last. Credit to the planning. England were aiming to score runs at a slightly quicker rate than before while South Africa were looking to restrict the run flow. Rabada angled this into the right-hander from over the wicket and it was a pretty innocuous delivery, with Sibley just looking to tuck it through the on side. But he did not realize that there is a man stationed at leg gully, where Dean Elgar took it. Sibley would be crestfallen. 94 balls before this, watchful batting, makes a mistake of not watching the field on the 95th. The 70-run opening stand is broken.

OUT! LBW! That is a sensational review from South Africa. England lose their third wicket. The review was taken with just 5 seconds left on the clock. But it is successful. Flighted delivery on middle, Denly looks to defend off the back foot and does so. Or, does he? Because to the naked eye, it is not clear whether the ball hit the bat first or pad. Maharaj appeals for lbw but umpire Bruce Oxenford shakes his head. Now, strangely, the men behind the wickets are not sure whether that is out. Shouldn't de Kock know about that? But Faf asks him and Quinton is mum. It is Maharaj who is dead sure that it is pad first. South Africa think for a while and eventually, du Plessis takes the review. Oxenford makes the signal and when his colleague at square leg asks him what was it, Bruce says that it hit the bat. The first look at the replays brings out a huge cheer from the crowd. Because it shows that the ball has hit ONLY the pad and there is no bat involved at all! Now, time for the Ball Tracker which shows all three reds, with the ball projected to be hitting the middle stump. What a review from Maharaj. He is single-handedly responsible for this wicket. Is this the opening which the hosts needed?

Back of a length ball on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot to point.
On a length on off, Ben solidly blocks it out to the cover fielder.
Rabada bends his back and bowls a short one outside off, Stokes pushes it to cover.
Fullish on middle and leg, Ben defends it towards mid on.
Rabada keeps on bowling short and this one is on middle, Stokes pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
BOUNCER! Good one from Rabada! Bowls it around off, Root though does very well to sway away from it.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery! Floated outside off, spinning into the batsman. Stokes looks to defend but it cuts him in half and goes into the mitts of the keeper.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call and Stokes survives! Maharaj looks in terrific form out there! A vast contrast from the previous game. Bowls a flighted one around off, Stokes looks to defend but misses to get hit on the front pad. Maharaj puts in an appeal but it is turned down by the umpire. Maharaj and Faf are involved in a discussion whether to go for a review or not. They opt for it. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it was umpire's call on impact. South Africa do not lose their review.
Flatter one on middle, Stokes whips it to the leg side for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Floated one on middle, Root sweeps it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
FOUR! Some innovation this time from Root! Full toss on middle, Root plays the paddle sweep to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Floated on middle, Root sweeps it to the deep mid-wicket region and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up. Drama in the over, with 11 runs and an LBW review.
On a good length on off, Stokes defends it uppishly towards point.
Outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to this one.
Short delivery on middle, Stokes pulls it through square leg for a single.
Short again on middle, Root pulls it to mid-wicket.

OUT! TIMBER! That kept low! Root has to go now! Big, big wicket and South Africa are making a comeback in this game. Back of a length delivery from Rabada. It is bowled on off, keeping a touch low and skidding through after pitching. Root misreads it, looking to defend it off the back foot but the ball sneaks under his bat and goes onto hit the off stump. So 103/1 becomes 148/4.
Short ball around middle, Pope ducks under it.

NOT OUT! No edge and the impact was outside off. The review is lost. Floated outside off from Maharaj spinning into the batsman, Stokes lunges and then looks to defend but it seems to have hit the pads. The ball goes to Zubayr Hamza at first slip. He collects and appeals. The umpire shows no interest. Faf is concerned this time, running in to ask about the review. Everyone is confident but Hamza is the most confident and the skipper, one feels, goes for a catch review. The Ultra Edge then rolls in and it shows that there was a big gap between the bat and pad. The Ball Tracker shows that the impact was outside off as well. It had hit just the pads and then gone to the first slip fielder. A review in desperation from Faf.
Floated delivery on middle, Stokes flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Tossed up delivery on leg, Pope looks to defend but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Flighted delivery on off, Pope defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Pope keeps it out.
FOUR! That is put away! Short and outside off, Pope cuts it hard through point for a boundary. 150 UP FOR ENGLAND.
A length ball outside off, from around the wicket, left alone.
Full and just outside off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes along the ground, towards point.
Fullish ball on off, Stokes pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Poor delivery and it has been rightfully put away by Stokes. Full toss on middle, Stokes whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
BOUNCER! WIDE! It is bowled around middle, Stokes ducks under it. The umpire gives it wide for height.

NO BALL! Nasty! Good length ball on off, Stokes looks to flick but misses and gets hit around the box. Seems fine to continue. Rabada has overstepped or has he? The replays show that it was a tight call. Hard to say whether the foot landed on the line while did the foot land inside and then skid through.
WIDE. That is a wild bouncer, way above the head of the batsman. Signalled so.
Short ball on middle, Stokes pulls it to the deep mid-wicket region for a single.
DROPPED! Tough chance. Fractionally short, around off, Stokes goes back and whips it. Pieter Malan at short leg reacts swiftly too. He sticks out his right hand but the ball does not stick.

FOUR! Another hit-me ball by Rabada and this brings up the 22nd Test fifty for Ben Stokes. Stokes again goes deep in his crease and pulls this ball towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. He is a man in scintillating form and is oozing class at the moment.

Loopy delivery on off, Pope plays it towards covers.
Floated delivery on middle, Pope drives it towards mid on where Rabada picks the ball and goes for a direct hit at the bowler's end but misses it. The batsmen take a single.

Chance missed! Nortje is the culprit! Loopy delivery on middle, Stokes comes down the track and lofts it over mid on but does not get the distance on it. It goes towards long on where Nortje tries to take the catch but it hits his fingertips and goes down. The batsmen take a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Stokes punches it through point. The batsmen cross ends. 200-run stand is up between Ben Stokes and Ollie Pope.
Length ball on off, pushed towards point.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Fullish ball on middle, pushed towards the man at mid on for a quick single.
Full ball on off, worked towards the man at mid on by Stokes.
Length ball on off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads.
Full ball on off, driven towards the man at cover for a single. 350 up for England with this single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Stokes keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Stokes drives it towards mid on.
Floated delivery on off, Stokes plays a reverse sweep towards cover.
Loopy delivery on middle, Stokes looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Pope blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball on off, pushed towards the man at mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! First Test wicket for Dane Paterson and he has struck gold as he has sent Ben Stokes packing. However, he has played a brilliant innings and done the damage. A nothing delivery outside off, Stokes goes for a wild slash at it but does so uppishly. Dean Elgar at point takes a simple catch to his right. Stokes trying to score some runs throws his wicket away but he has more than done his job. He departs after scoring a solid century and will be hoping that his teammates carry the good work from here on in. Can the Proteas force a collapse from here though?
Buttler plays this one towards the cover region off the back foot.
Length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards the man at mid on.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted delivery on middle, Pope defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Pope drives it through mid off for a run.
Floated delivery on off, Buttler plays it towards point.
Loopy delivery on off, Jos plays it to covers.
Flighted delivery on middle, Buttler blocks it off the front foot.
On off, Buttler pushes it towards covers for a single.
On a good length on off, Buttler blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Jos keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Buttler defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Buttler defends it out.
On a length on off, Buttler drives it to mid off.
Length delivery outside off, Buttler taps it to point.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pope flicks it towards fine leg for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Buttler has literally thrown his wicket away and England lose wickets in quick succession. Tossed up delivery on off, Buttler looks to punch it down the ground but does so uppishly and straight towards Maharaj who takes an easy catch. Buttler will be very disappointed by this soft dismissal. Can the Proteas take advantage here and wrap up the tail before they reach 400?

Almost another one! Floated delivery on the pads, Curran looks to work it towards the leg side but does so a touch uppishly. The fielder at short leg dives to his right but the ball goes past him by then.
On off, played towards cover.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

A loud appeal has been turned down! Now, what has happened there? Maharaj bowls a flatter delivery from around the wicket, pitching it outside off, angling it into Curran. Curran looks to defend but is hit on the pads. The South African players appeal but it is turned down by the umpire. They cannot do anything about it as the Proteas have no reviews left. Replays later roll in and show that the ball was going on to hit the leg pole but the impact was umpire's call. So, Curran would have been safe anyway.
On a good length on off, Pope defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Pope drives it towards mid off.
Short delivery outside off, Pope cuts it to point.
On a length on middle, Pope flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Length delivery on middle, Curran flicks it through square leg for a run.
On a good length on off, Pope defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Curran flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off, Curran defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Sam keeps it out.
Floated delivery on middle, Curran looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards fine leg. The batsmen get two runs. The umpire gives it as leg byes.
Tossed up delivery on off, Curran defends it out.
On middle, Curran flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full delivery on off, Curran drives it to covers.
On a good length on off, Curran blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Sam blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full delivery on off, Curran drives it uppishly wide of the man at short covers for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Curran blocks it off the front foot.
Short delivery outside off, Curran cuts it through point for a run.
Floated delivery on middle and off, defended out.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Curran comes down the track and plays this ball back towards the bowler.
On the pads, flicked towards the fine leg region. Pretorius gives it a chase and keeps the ball in play as the batters take three runs.
Floated on off, pushed towards the cover region for a single.
Length ball outside off, cut towards point for a single.
Full length ball on middle and leg, defended back towards the bowler.
Length ball on middle and off, defended back towards the bowler.
Good length ball just outside the off pole line, defended out.
Good fielding! Full ball on off, driven towards the man at cover-point where Rassie van der Dussen dives to his right and makes the stop. Saves at least a couple of runs for his side.
FOUR! Driven away! Full ball on off, Curran has creamed his drive through the cover region for a boundary. Fantastic shot that!
Tossed up delivery on leg, Pope looks to flick but gets it off the thigh pad. It goes towards the keeper where de Kock appeals for caught behind but the umpire shakes his head.
Flighted delivery on middle, Pope blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Pope has planted his foot just inches inside the crease and he survives. Floated delivery outside off, Maharaj gets this to turn away from Pope after pitching. Ollie goes for the drive but misses due to the turn. De Kock behind the stumps collects the ball and whips the bails off and appeals. The leg umpire half-heartedly goes to the third umpire and the Proteas players don't look that excited either. Replays roll in to show that Pope had brought his foot in a while before de Kock whipped the bails off and he survives.
Floated on off, pushed towards the man at mid off.
Outside off, played towards the man at point.
On a good length on off, Curran defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Curran blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Sam offers a solid defense on this one.
Short and outside off, Curran cuts it through point for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Pope drives it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
Good length delivery on middle, Pope blocks it off the front foot.
SIX! What a shot! Flighted delivery on middle, Curran comes down the track and lofts it over long on for a maximum.
Floated delivery on middle, Sam tucks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Curran flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Loopy delivery on middle, Pope comes down the track and drives it towards mid on for a single.
Flighted delivery outside off, Curran punches it through covers. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a length on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short and outside off, Pope cuts it through point for a single.
On a good length on off, Curran defends it off the back foot.
EDGE AND FOUR! Full and outside off, Curran looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Short delivery on off, Sam looks to pull but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Length delivery outside off, Curran plays it towards the off side.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pope drives it towards mid on.
Flighted delivery on off, Pope keeps it out.
Floated delivery on middle, Pope comes down the track and blocks it.
Loopy delivery on off, Pope comes down the track and drives it through mid off for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Curran plays it to point.
FOUR! Nicely played! Flighted delivery on middle, Curran comes down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
Full delivery on leg, Pope looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Short and outside off, Pope cuts it through point. Rabada slides and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get two runs. Ollie Pope moves to 90s.
On a good length on off, Pope blocks it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Pope plays it to covers.
Short of a length delivery, Pope pulls it over square leg. The fielder in the deep collects the ball on one bounce. The batsmen take a single.
Good length delivery on off, Sam blocks it well.
Short and outside off, Curran cuts it through point. The batsmen take a run. 400 up for England.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Curran flicks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery on middle, Curran sweeps it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Flighted delivery on off, Curran lofts it over mid off. Rabada at long off picks the ball on one bounce. The batsmen take a run.
Full delivery on off, Pope drives it through mid off for a single. 50-run stand is up between Ollie Pope and Sam Curran.
Tossed up delivery on off, Curran drives it through mid off. The batsmen cross ends.
FOUR! Dragged back ball on off, Curran rocks back and slams this one through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Curran goes back and defends it from within the crease.
FOUR! Down the ground! Floated delivery on off, Curran comes down the ground and has smashed that one down the ground through mid off for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Curran holes out but he has played an entertaining innings and given the England score a booster. Floated delivery on off, Curran looks to come down the track and clear the mid-wicket fence. It is the larger side of the ground and that is why, Elgar comes in a couple of steps from the deep and takes an easy catch. Another wicket for South Africa and a deserved one for Maharaj.
Pope comes down the track and plays this one towards the cover region.
Outside off, played towards deep point for a single.
On a length and outside off, Pope drives it through point for a single. He moves to 96.
On a good length on off, Bess defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on middle, Bess flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Pope drives it towards mid on.
On a length on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Maiden Test ton for Ollie Pope. It has been a terrific innings from him. He has grinded it out in the middle and he pumps his fists in the air in delight. A floated delivery on middle, Pope comes down the track and flicks it through the mid-wicket region for a boundary. He had been stuck between the 80s ever since Stokes departed but now that he has got to his ton, Pope will be looking to accelerate and end with a flurry.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Bess looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery just outside off, Bess looks to defend but misses it.
Loopy delivery on off, Bess offers a forward defense on this one.
Floated delivery on off, Bess plays it to point.
On middle, Bess defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on off, Bess plays it towards point.
Length delivery down the leg side, Pope looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on off, Pope guides it towards short third man.
FOUR! Whoa! What a shot! Bouncer on middle and off pole, Pope opens the face of the bat and just guides this over the keeper's head for a boundary into the third man fence.
Full delivery on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, Pope plays it towards covers for a run.
Good length delivery on middle, Bess blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pope flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pieter Malan takes an easy catch and Keshav Maharaj gets another wicket. Floated delivery on the leg pole line, Bess looks to work this one towards the leg side but the ball goes off the leading edge towards the right of silly point where Pieter Malan takes an easy catch. Bess goes back without troubling the scorers much and England have just two wickets left now. And with that, it will be TEA ON DAY 2!
BEATEN! Tossed up delivery outside off, Wood looks to defend but misses it.
Flighted delivery on off, Wood plays it towards point.
Loopy delivery on middle, Wood blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Wood offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Pope defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Pope drives it uppishly towards mid off.
Length delivery on off, Ollie taps it to point.

Whoa! What has happened there? Short of a length delivery on leg, Pope looks to pull but fails to do so. Quinton de Kock appeals for a caught behind but the umpire shakes his head. The Proteas seem pretty confident that there was something on that as the ball came to de Kock but they do not have any reviews left. Replays show that it came off the glove. The loss of reviews earlier in the innings has cost South Africa here.
Bowls a bouncer, Pope does well to duck under it.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short of a length delivery, Pope pulls it over square leg for a boundary.
SIX! Amazing shot. Tossed up delivery on middle, Bess plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a maximum.
FOUR! Good shot. Floated delivery on middle, Wood sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Loopy delivery on middle, Wood looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Wood defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Wood looks to loft it but gets a top edge. It lands safely towards covers. The batsmen get two runs.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full delivery on middle, Pope drives it through mid on but Ollie Pope does not take the single.
Length delivery on off, Pope taps it to point.
On a good length on middle, Pope blocks it off the back foot.
On a length on off, Pope punches it towards the off side.
Short delivery down the leg side, Pope looks to pull but misses it.
Bowls a bouncer, Pope does well to duck under it. It goes towards the keeper where de Kock collects it safely behind the stumps. The batsmen steal a bye.
Floated on off, Pope plays the reverse sweep but straight to the fielder at short third man.
Outside off, quicker delivery, played towards point for a single.
SIX! Meaty blow! Floated delivery on middle and leg, Wood clears his front leg and smashes this ball over the long on region for a maximum.
Floated on off, swept fine towards the leg side for a single.
Reverse sweep played by the batsman. One run added to the total.
SIX! Another huge one! This time it is floated on the leg pole line, again Wood clears his front leg and hammers it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie. Second of the over.
Short delivery outside off, Pope cuts it through point but does not take the single.
FOUR! Nice improvisation. On a length on off, Pope plays a reverse paddle scoop over the keeper's head towards fine leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Another one! Ben Stokes is looking in disbelief at all this! Good length ball on middle and off, Pope gets down and paddles it over the third man region for a boundary.
Pope has played it fine down the leg side. The batsmen have run through for a single.

NO BALL! NOT OUT! Rabada had dismissed Wood, Root had signalled for the declaration and Wood was running off the ground but after the umpire referred upstairs, replays show that Rabada has overstepped. Short of a length delivery, Wood looks to pull but gets a top edge on that one. It goes high in the air and Nortje takes a comfortable catch at mid-wicket. However, after seeing the replays that Rabada has overstepped, the umpire asks Root whether he wants to declare or not and the England skipper decides to rub salt into the wounds of the Proteas and continue to swell their score.
The batsman has top edged that one.
FOUR! Punched off the back foot by the batsman. The ball has crossed the ropes.
Flighted delivery on off, Pope plays a reverse sweep towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
Tossed up delivery on off, Pope defends it towards point.
Short delivery on middle, Maharaj pulls it over mid-wicket for a run.

SIX! Wood has smashed that one! Length ball on middle, Wood goes back and has smashed that one over the long on region for a maximum. Shouts of catch it but the only ones catching this one will be the crowd.
Wood goes for a wild swing but misses the ball completely.
The batsman fails to put bat on ball.
On a good length on off, Pope punches it through covers. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Full delivery on off, Pope drives it towards mid off.
Short delivery on middle, Pope pulls it over mid on.
EDGED AND SIX! Length ball down the leg side, Pope looks to flick it but the ball goes off the top edge and into the fine leg fence for a maximum.
Bouncer on middle, Pope looks to go for the upper cut initially but then backs away.
Another bouncer, this time outside off, Pope plays the upper cut over the slip cordon and they get a single as now there is a man standing right behind the fine leg region.
Floated on off, pushed towards cover for a single.
SIX! Wood is going hammer and tongs here! Floated on middle and off, Wood gets down on one knee and smashes this one into the mid-wicket fence for a huge maximum.
Wood again goes down on one knee and slaps this one towards mid-wicket for a single.
Floated on off, smashed towards the cover region for a single.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Anrich Nortje now takes the catch and Keshav Maharaj gets his 5-fer too. And that will be that as England have now declared! A floated delivery on middle and leg, Wood again looks to clear the long on fence but mistimes and holes out as Nortje completes the catch. This time no retake as Maharaj is safe. ENGLAND DECLARE ON 499/9!
Broad starts with a full delivery on middle, Elgar drives it towards mid on showing the full face of the bat.
On a length and outside off, Elgar guides it towards third man. The batsmen get two runs. South Africa are underway!
Length delivery on off, Elgar taps it towards point.
FOUR! A good length ball outside off, Elgar opens the face of the bat and guides it in the gap between point and gully and the ball races away to the backward point fence. Elgar is off the mark!
Length ball on off, Elgar rocks back and defends.
Another length ball on middle and off, defended by Elgar.
Length ball just outside off, defended out by Malan.
This time it is on a back of a length and outside off, Malan leaves it alone.
Malan rocks back and defends this good length ball from within the crease.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On the hips of Malan, he works it towards the fine leg region and gets a couple.
Length ball way outside off, Malan will not fiddle with it.
Length ball on middle and off, defended towards the off side by Elgar.
Length ball just outside off, Elgar is confident exactly where his stumps are and makes the leave.

Almost! Broad producing a jaffa here! Bowling a ball on a length just outside off, it straightens a touch after pitching. Elgar looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge towards second slip. The ball falls just short of Ben Stokes there and Elgar survives.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards the man at mid on.
On the pads, worked towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Pieter Malan goes onto the back foot and defends the ball showing the full face of the bat.
FOUR! On the pads, Malan flicks this towards the square leg region and bags a boundary.
Length ball on middle and off, blocked out by Malan.
Good length ball on off, Pieter does well to defend this one.
Fullish ball on off, defended towards the man at cover.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by the batsman.
On a good length on off, Elgar defends it off the back foot.
On a length on off, Elgar pushes it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Elgar looks to defend but misses it.
FOUR! On a good length on off, Elgar looks to defend but gets it off the outer half of the bat. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Elgar defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Elgar drives it towards mid on.
FOUR! Poor delivery from Curran. On a length on leg, Malan flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Malan defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Malan keeps it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Malan defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Malan flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, Malan blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Elgar pushes it towards the off side.
FOUR! Cracking shot. Short and outside off, Elgar cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
Length delivery on middle, Elgar flicks it through square leg for a single.
On a good length on off, Malan taps it towards covers and takes a quick single.
Full delivery on middle, Elgar drives it towards mid on.
On a good length on off, Elgar blocks it off the back foot.
Starts with a floated delivery on middle and leg, worked towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, pushed towards the man at cover.
This time darted fuller on the off pole line, defended out.
Floated delivery on middle and off, defended.

Gorgeous delivery by Bess! He gives it a lot of air and lands it on off, Elgar looks to defend but the ball spins away and beats the outside edge of Elgar's bat. Clear signs of spin here on this track and maybe of interest to skipper Joe Root as well.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
On the hips of Malan, he flicks this one fine towards the leg side and gets a single.
Outside off, played towards point.
FOUR! Another one which is on the pads, Elgar tickles it fine down the leg side for a boundary. Easy runs!
Length ball on off, punched towards the cover region off the back foot for a couple.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Second one of the over! Length ball just outside off, Elgar opens the face of his bat and guides it fine down the third man region for a boundary.
On the pads of Malan, Bess looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Floated delivery on off, Malan opens the face of his bat and guides it just wide of the man at first slip towards the third man region for a couple.
Drags his length back does Bess, Malan defends it off the back foot.
Played to the point region by the batsman. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Floated on middle and off, driven towards mid on and Elgar takes an easy single.
On a good length on off, Elgar taps it towards point.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full delivery on off, Elgar drives it through covers for a single.
Full on middle, Elgar drives it towards mid on.
Good length delivery on off, Elgar blocks it off the front foot.
On a length on off, Dean plays it towards point.
Length delivery on off, Dean taps it towards point.
Quicker delivery on middle and leg, Malan goes back and defends.
Floated on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Loopy delivery on off, Malan opens the face of his bat and guides this one down to third man for a couple.
Flighted delivery on middle, Malan flicks it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery on off, Malan plays it towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Dominic Bess has provided the breakthrough exactly when it looked like South Africa were getting at least one foot in the game. Floated delivery on middle and off pole line, Malan looks to come down the track and looks to defend it back to Malan but instead he scoops it back to Bess who takes a dolly. The umpire is not sure whether the ball bounced before hitting the bat or after and goes upstairs. Replays roll in and show that the ball pitched first and Malan has just scooped that back to Bess. Timely breakthrough for the visitors.
Length ball on middle and off to start by Wood, Elgar defends it back towards the bowler.
Again Elgar goes onto the back foot and defends it.
Elgar again rocks back and defends it from within the crease although very awkwardly.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Bouncer on middle and leg, ducked under.
OUCH! Length ball on middle and leg, angling into Elgar. Dean looks to make room and pull but the ball hits his hand. That must have hurt him and he is on his haunches right now.
Tossed up delivery on off, Malan defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Hamza blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Hamza flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated delivery on off, Hamza defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full delivery on off, Hamza drives it through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Hamza comes forward and looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
On a good length on off, Elgar blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Elgar flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short delivery on off, Elgar stands tall and defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Elgar defends it towards the off side.
Good length delivery on middle, Dean blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Elgar looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Hamza flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Elgar defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Elgar blocks it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Elgar keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Elgar defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Elgar blocks it well.
Woah! What a bouncer now! Bouncer on middle and leg, Hamza somehow gets on top of it and dabs it onto the ground.
Another one! Hamza this time just about manages to sway away from the line of the bouncer. Wood is bowling some brutal bouncers here.
EDGED AND FOUR! Length delivery angling into Hamza, on the leg pole line, he looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge and into the fine leg fence.
Length ball on off, Hamza pushes this one towards the cover region off the back foot and gets a single.
Length ball on middle and leg, Elgar looks to flick but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
Length ball on middle and off, defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Flighted delivery on middle, Hamza defends it off the front foot.
Bess bowls it down the leg side, Hamza lets it go.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ollie Pope has taken the catch and South Africa have lost their second wicket. Floated delivery on middle and leg, Hamza looks to go back and work this one towards the leg side but the ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads and towards short leg where Ollie Pope comes forward and takes a simple catch. Another wicket taken by Bess and he is making some early inroads in the South African batting line-up.
Floated delivery on middle, Nortje prods forward and defends.
On the pads, worked away with a wristy shot towards the leg side.
Floated delivery on middle and leg, well defended by Nortje. Does well to negotiate the over.
Beauty to start the day! A good length ball just outside off, it shapes away after pitching. Elgar looks to defend but gets a bit squared up. Luckily for him, it does not take the outside edge.
Good follow up ball. It is shortish and on off, Elgar awkwardly keeps it out off the outer half of the bat.
Beaten! Another good length ball around off, Elgar looks to defend but misses once again.
On the stumps line, it is defended towards short leg.
Another ball which is on the stumps, Elgar comes forward and pushes it to mid on.
Length ball on middle, Elgar looks to work it on the leg side but it takes the outer half of the bat and goes towards covers. A maiden over to start the day.
Floated ball around off, Nortje comes forward and defends it out.
Flatter one on the pads, Nortje tucks it towards leg gully where the fielder makes a diving stop.
On middle, another front foot defense from Nortje.
Another ball which is around off and middle, Nortje keeps it out.
Down the leg side. Nortje lets it go to the keeper.
Slightly shortish ball around off, Nortje pushes it back to the bowler to see off the over.
Slightly shortish and around off and middle, Elgar goes on the back foot and keeps it out.
Around off on a good length, Elgar guides it to the man at gully with an angled bat.

Back of a length ball on the body now, Elgar was in two minds, whether to go for the pull or let it be. He eventually goes for the pull but does not connect it well. Luckily the mistimed pull goes to fine leg for a single. First runs of the morning.
In the channel outside off for the right-hander. Nortje lets is be.
Fuller and around off, it is pushed to mid off.
A length ball outside off, Nortje covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Tossed up on off, Elgar makes room and punches it through covers. Wood chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
Flighted delivery on off, Elgar looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes safely towards first slip on one bounce.
Loopy delivery on middle, Elgar blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! Caught! Sharp catch from Ollie Pope. A massive wicket for England early in the day. Bess bowls it around off and middle, Elgar comes forward to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and hits the pad. It lobs towards Pope at silly point. He dives forward and grabs the ball inches above the turf. The South Africans appeal and the umpire agrees. Very, very sharp grab from Pope. Elgar is one of those batters who can dig in deep but he has been removed. One can say that this wicket belongs to the fielder there than the bowler.

OUT! Caught! The skipper is out of here and it is once again the Bess and Pope combination. No. 4 is down and all of them has fallen to Bess. Du Plessis was attacking him in this over, seeing that Bess drags his length slightly behind. Du Plessis once again comes out of his crease and looks to defend. However, the ball takes an inside edge, hits the pads and goes to Pope at silly point once again. It goes straight to him and he is not going to miss out on such an easy chance. Umpire there seem to be not lifting his finger but du Plessis knew that there was bat so he started walking himself. Brilliant, brilliant bowling from Bess and England are on top of this game.

Tossed up delivery on leg, Philander looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Full delivery on middle, Philander drives it towards mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Philander drives it through mid on for a run.
Loopy delivery on off, Keshav defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Maharaj keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, Maharaj blocks it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Philander blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Philander defends it out.
Bowls a bouncer, Philander does well to duck under it.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Philander looks to defend but misses it.
Bowls a bumper, Philander ducks under it.
Bowls a bouncer, Philander lets it sail through to the keeper.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Maharaj defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Maharaj blocks it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Maharaj punches it to point.

Tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Maharaj looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Later on Ball Tracker shows that it would have been umpire's call. Both the teams don't have any reviews.
Floated delivery on off, Maharaj blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Maharaj blocks it well.
Short ball down the leg side, Philander looks to pull but it takes the gloves and the ball goes rolling to the keeper.
Shortish in length on middle and leg, Philander pulls it to square leg where Stokes makes a good diving stop.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Philander ducks under it.
Short delivery on middle, Philander pulls it towards square leg.
WIDE! Bowls a bouncer, Philander ducks under it.
On a good length on middle, Philander blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, Philander shoulders arms to this one.
Tossed up delivery on off, Maharaj defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Maharaj plays it towards covers for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Philander defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Philander plays it towards mid off.
On off, Philander blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Tossed up delivery on middle, Philander flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full delivery outside off, Maharaj shoulders arms to it.
EDGY! Full delivery on off, Maharaj looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and the ball goes through the gully region for a couple.
Good length ball on off, Maharaj is solid in defense and goes so towards cover. The batters take a single.
Back of a length ball on middle and leg, Philander works it to the leg side.

DROPPED! Stokes and his butter fingers! Short of a length ball on the pads, Philander pulls but it goes straight into the hands of Stokes at square leg. The ball goes quickly to him causing him to drop it.
Good length ball down the leg side, Philander looks to flick but misses it altogether. Wood appeals for a caught behind but the umpire gives it not out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Maharaj defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Maharaj blocks it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on off, Maharaj plays it towards covers for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Philander keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Philander nudges it towards the leg side.
Flatter one one middle and leg, Maharaj works it to square leg.
Floated on off, Maharaj defends it off the front foot to cover.
Loopy delivery on middle, Maharaj defends it to the leg side.
Flatter delivery down the leg side. Maharaj shoulders arms to this one.
Floated delivery on middle, Maharaj flicks it towards the leg side.
Bess bowls it down the leg side, Maharaj lets it go. Umpires have said that one more over can be bowled.
FOUR! Poor delivery! Floated on the pads, Philander just helps it on its way to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Floated on middle, Philander whips it to the leg side for a single.
Flighted on middle, defended out by Maharaj.
Looped up ball on middle, Maharaj defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Maharaj blocks it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Maharaj keeps it out. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Broad starts with a good length delivery just around off, defended by Philander.
This time it is on a length outside off, left alone by Philander.

OUT! CAUGHT! There is the breakthrough and that too in the first over on Day 5. Stuart Broad has again sent Philander packing and England looking to wrap it up quickly. Good length ball nipping back in, Philander looks to defend but the ball comes off the inside edge onto the pads and goes aerially towards short mid-wicket. Ollie Pope there dives forward and takes a good catch. Victory within touching distance for England.
Fullish length ball around off, pushed towards the man at mid on.
Good length ball on off, defended back towards the bowler.
EDGED AND FOUR! Full length ball on off, Rabada looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge past the man at first slip and into the third man fence.
Maharaj has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads, worked towards square leg for one.
Superb delivery by Root! Floated on off, Rabada looks to defend but the ball turns away and beats the outside edge of Rabada's bat.
Rabada prods forward and defends.
Another edge is induced as the ball pitches on off and turns away. It flies away from the man at second slip and the batters take two.
Rabada again defends solidly off the front foot to get through the over.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Maharaj.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
This time on a length and closer to the body, Maharaj stands tall and defends.
Outside off again, left alone by Keshav.
Good length ball just outside off, Maharaj defends this one towards the off side.
Another good length ball on off, Maharaj defends it towards the man at cover.
Root bowls this one just around off, Rabada defends.
Another one on off, defended towards the off side.

SIX! Woah! Rabada surely can bat and that shot proves it! Floated delivery on off, Rabada gets down on one knee and has just lofted it beautifully over the long off region for a biggie. Class shot, full of grace!
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated on off, Rabada defends it towards the cover region.
Last ball of the over and Rabada defends it towards point. Root will be aching for a 5-fer here.
Good length ball on off, defended towards the man at short extra cover by Maharaj.
Maharaj prods forward and defends this full ball confidently.
Outside off, left alone.
Maharaj defends this full ball on off towards the man at short extra cover again.
Very full ball on off, almost a yorker, well defended by Maharaj.
The batsman has attempted to put bat on ball but fails.
Floated delivery on off, defended by Rabada.

Woah! Looked like a dropped catch but no edge on it. The ball just turned that much! Tossed up delivery around off, Rabada looks to defend but the ball turns away and misses the outside edge. The keeper fails to collect and it looked like a dropped catch but there was no edge on that.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Shortish delivery outside off, Rabada looks to cut but misses.
Rabada has confidently driven this ball towards the man at mid off.
Another full ball on off, driven towards the man at mid off again.
Back of a length ball on off, Maharaj ducks. The ball was nowhere near him though and only he will know why he ducked.
Another back of a length, this time directed on the body of Maharaj. He does not duck this time and the ball goes off his glove towards fine leg and the batters cross ends.
The batsman has driven it through mid off.
FOUR! Driven away! Full ball on middle and off, Rabada has driven it through mid on for a boundary.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Rabada prods forward and does well to defend this ball. Gets through another over.
A bit shortish ball on middle, defended by Maharaj.
Again Maharaj rocks back and defends the ball onto the pitch.
FOUR! Up and over! Floated delivey on middle, Maharaj has lofted this delivery over the man at mid on for a boundary.
Root bowls it fuller down the leg side, Maharaj goes back and dabs it onto the pitch.
FOUR! Good application by the batters here! Tossed up delivery on off, Maharaj carves it through the point region for a boundary.
Maharaj has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

OUT! CAUGHT! Wood comes into the attack and strikes straightaway! Good length ball on middle and leg, it is a cross-seam delivery. Rabada looks to flick it towards the leg side but the ball goes off the leading edge uppishly towards mid on where Stuart Broad takes an easy catch. 2 wickets to go for an England victory.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Another one which is just outside off, left alone again by Nortje.
Good length ball on middle and off, Anrich looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads.
Back of a length ball on middle. Nortje defends.
Good length ball on middle, Nortje has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated delivery on off, driven towards the man at mid off.
Maharaj prods forward and defends solidly.
On off, solidly defended.
Beaten! Tossed up delivery on off, Maharaj looks to cut but the ball stays low and turns in to beat the bat of Maharaj.
Another one which turns in and stays low, Maharaj defends.
Down the leg side, Maharaj lets it be.
Back of a length ball on off, Nortje dabs it onto the pitch.
Length ball on middle and off, punched off the back foot towards mid on.
Back of a length ball on off, left alone.
Another length ball outside off, left alone by Nortje.
Back of a length ball on middle, defended onto the pitch by Anrich.
Another back of a length ball on the body, Nortje defends.
Floated delivery on off, defended towards mid off.
Down the leg side, Maharaj plays it onto the pitch.
On middle and leg, Maharaj goes back and defends.
This time it is outside off, Maharaj looks to cut but misses. The keeper also misses the ball and the ball goes behind him and the batters take a bye.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
EDGED AND FOUR! Floated delivery on off, Nortje looks to punch it towards the off side but the ball goes off the inside edge past short leg for a boundary.
What a bouncer! No one has been able to extract this kind of bounce from the surface except Wood. At a speed of 143 kph, Wood bowls a bouncer on middle and Maharaj does well to get out of the way.
Good length ball just around off, defended by Maharaj.
FOUR! Cut away! Back of a length ball on off, Maharaj rocks back and cuts behind point for a boundary.
Another bouncer and Maharaj does well to get down and let it go.
Almost! Back of a length ball on off, Maharaj hops and looks to defend but the ball goes off the splice of the bat behind silly point and falls safe. Chance but no one there!
Length ball on middle and off, defended back towards the bowler.
Very full ball on middle and leg, Nortje defends.
Down the leg side, worked towards fine leg for one.
Quicker delivery on middle, defended back towards Root.
Way down the leg side, left alone by Root.
Maharaj rocks back and defends this ball on the middle pole line.
Another flatter delivery and Maharaj negotiates through another over.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated delivery on off, Nortje does well to defend.
Nortje rocks back and defends this ball towards the leg side.

OUT! BOWLED! Dominic Bess gets a wicket and another change of bowling works for Joe Root. Floated delivery on off, Nortje looks to go back and work this one towards the leg side but the ball goes through bat and pad and into the stumps. England just one wicket away from the victory.
Another delivery which spins in from outside off, Paterson looks to defend but is hit on the pads. Looks to be going down leg.
Paterson has flicked the ball off his pads. A successful over for the England team ends.
Down the leg side, Maharaj works it towards the leg side.
On the pads, worked towards square leg for one.
Paterson has driven this one through the covers for a couple.
Floated on middle, pushed towards the man at mid on.
Floated on off, pushed towards the man at mid off now.
FOUR! No fear from Paterson! Floated delivery on off, Paterson lofts this one over the mid off fielder for a boundary.
Floated delivery on middle and leg, Maharaj looks to defend but is hit on the pad.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Maharaj pushes it towards the man at mid off and takes a single.
Paterson goes back in his crease and defends.

Good fielding! This one is floated outside off by Bess, Paterson cuts it towards backward point where Root runs after it and saves a run for his side as he dives to keep the ball in play. Replays confirm that Root has stopped it cleanly. Good effort by the skipper!
Floated on middle, driven towards the man at mid on.
Shortish ball on middle, Paterson rocks back and defends it onto the pitch.
Very full ball on middle, jammed out towards point and the batters take a run.
The batsman has driven that ball straight back past the bowler. One run added to the total.
Paterson defends this by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR BYES! Down the leg side, Maharaj goes after it and misses. The ball goes through everyone and into the fine leg fence.
Floated on middle and off, defended by Paterson.
On off, defended solidly.
Paterson goes back and defends it solidly.
FOUR! Good batting by Paterson! Well outside off this one, Dane goes back and cuts this one through point for a boundary.
On the pads, defended towards the leg side.
Outside off, Paterson slices the ball towards third man and gets a couple.
FOUR! Root floats one on middle and off, Maharaj goes down on one knee and sweeps through the square leg region for a boundary.
FOUR! Another one! Down the leg side, Maharaj looks to flick this one down the leg side and the ball goes off the inside edge towards the fine leg fence.
FOUR! 3 in a row! Tossed up on middle, Maharaj has swept that one through the backward square leg region for a boundary.
SIX! Whack! What a shot by Keshav Maharaj! He goes down on one knee and has slogged this one into the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
SIX! Another slog sweep and this results in a maximum as well. Maharaj giving England a taste of their own medicine. Keshav plays the slog sweep and has hammered this one into the stands.
FOUR BYES! A googly which deceives Maharaj as well as Buttler. Floated on off, Maharaj looks to defend but the ball turns away beating the outside edge and Buttler as the ball goes into the fence.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Shortish ball on off, Paterson cuts it towards point and the batters take three.

Down the leg side, Maharaj does not offer the shot and the ball stays low. It beats Buttler as well and goes into the fine leg fence but because Maharaj did not offer the shot that is why no runs given.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. One run added to the total.
Floated delivery on off, chipped towards Broad at long off for a single.

FOUR! 50 up for Keshav Maharaj. His 2nd in Test matches although not much to enjoy about. On his pads, he has flicked this through the square leg region for a boundary. The 50-run stand is also up with this boundary.
Length ball outside off, Paterson looks to cut but misses.
FOUR! These two are providing some entertainment at the end now. 200 up for South Africa with this! Full ball on off, Paterson has lofted this one over the cover region and crosses the fence.
Length ball outside off, Paterson looks to heave but misses.
Again Paterson goes for a wild heave but misses.
The ball has taken the inside edge of the batsman and thudded into his pads.

Back of a length ball on off, Paterson pushes it towards the cover region but the man there misfields. The batters look for the second but Paterson is sent back. He makes it in with a dive as Pope whips the bails off at the non-striker's end.
Back of a length ball on the body, defended by Paterson awkwardly.
Bouncer on middle and off now, Paterson does well to leave that one.
Full ball on off, driven towards the man at mid off.
Bouncer on middle, Paterson looks to play the upper cut but misses.
Another bouncer on off, Paterson again goes for the upper cut but cannot get bat on ball.
Good length ball outside off, Paterson looks to slash at it but misses. Paterson is disgusted with himself as he misses out on that. Ambitious!

Full ball on middle and off, Maharaj lofts this one over mid off. The fielder at mid off runs back to catch the ball but cannot get to it despite a full-stretch dive. They manage to come back for the second.
SIX! Woah! What a shot that one! Full ball on the pads, Maharaj just flicks it away with a short-arm jab and the ball goes into the mid-wicket stands.
FOUR! This time Maharaj gets the best connection on a full ball on off as he clears the man at mid off and the ball crosses the fence.
Curran bowls a yorker on middle and off, Maharaj does well to keep it out.
FOUR! On the pads, Maharaj again flicks it, this time behind square leg for a boundary. This is superb batting by Maharaj!
Bouncer on middle and off, Maharaj looks to hook but misses.
Very full ball on off, Paterson plays this one towards point and takes one.
Bouncer on middle and off, Maharaj tries hooking that one but misses it completely.
FOUR! Back of a length ball on off, Maharaj rocks back and slaps this one over the man at cover for a boundary. Difficult shot but he has done well to execute that one.
Just short! Another back of a length ball on middle, Maharaj looks to pull but the ball goes off the inside half and falls just short of short mid-wicket where Ollie Pope is stationed.
Good length ball outside off, Maharaj swings but misses.
Back of a length ball on off and a rare defensive stroke by Maharaj.
Back of a length ball on off, Paterson looks to cut but misses.
FOUR! Another back of a length ball on off, Paterson goes hard at it but the ball goes off the edge and into the third man fence.
FOUR! Now an intentional one! Back of a length ball on off, Paterson has now lofted this over the slip cordon and the ball goes into the third man fence.
Good length ball on off, Paterson looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Loud appeal by England but has been turned down! Length ball on off, Paterson looks to cut but fails to do so. The ball is collected by Buttler and the England players appeal but it is turned down by the umpire.
FOUR! Lofted over! Back of a length ball on off, Paterson has superbly lofted this one over the man at point and the ball crosses the ropes. The stand moves on to 99 runs with this boundary.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Maharaj looks to slam at this one but the ball comes off the inside edge and onto the pads.
Outside off, Maharaj looks to slash at it but misses.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Maharaj ducks under it.
Full ball on off, driven towards the man at cover.

OUT! RUN OUT! Sam Curran has done the job, not with the ball but with his throw and ENGLAND WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 53 RUNS. A very low full toss on middle and leg, played down towards mid on and Maharaj sets off for a run. Sam Curran runs in, collects the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end. He hits with Maharaj running a bit across and not straight. The umpire goes upstairs but it looks out to the naked eye. Replays roll in and confirm that Maharaj is indeed well short. The partnership ends on 99 runs.
